              <p class="text-[#D4D4D4]">The expanding Nashville Pike corridor and the retail developments along US-31E feature new white TPO and EPDM roofing membranes that grease runoff will quickly damage. Meanwhile, the high-volume franchises and college-adjacent cafes near Volunteer State Community College push their exhaust fans hard enough to snap cheap OEM belts within months. When the first early-summer heatwave hits, aging and underpowered motors fail under the combined load of ambient roof temperature and continuous fryer output.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-heading text-white text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Two Environments, One Standard</h3>
