            <p class="text-[#D4D4D4]">The <strong class="text-white">Gallatin Fire Department Fire Prevention Division</strong> enforces NFPA 96 with particular intensity in the historic downtown overlay, where shared brick walls make grease duct fires a catastrophic risk to the entire block. Inspectors verify bare-metal cleanliness, confirm fire-rated access panels at every duct direction change, check hinge kit functionality on rooftop fans, and review current service documentation. Establishments failing inspection face mandatory remediation or temporary cooking shutdowns.</p>
            <p class="text-[#D4D4D4]"><strong class="text-white">Gallatin Public Utilities</strong> enforces local wastewater codes that extend to rooftop grease containment. If grease traps or rooftop catchers overflow into the municipal sewer system, the resulting F.O.G. violations carry significant fines. This creates a dual compliance requirement — your rooftop containment must satisfy both fire codes and wastewater regulations simultaneously.</p>
